  "abstract": "Twenty-one SSR loci data on 852 accessions were analyzed. This composite collection showed\r\nrich allelic diversity (490 alleles, 23.3 alleles per locus, 246 common alleles and 244 rare alleles\r\nat 1%), group-specific unique alleles, and common alleles sharing between subspecies and\r\ngeographical groups. Gene diversity ranged from 0.559 to 0.926, with an average of 0.819.\r\nUnique alleles are those detected in a group of accessions\r\n....................",
